{
  "text": "The functionalized Fe3O4 nanoparticles were mixed in mineral oil under continuous stirring with constant speed. Four different concentration samples of ferrofluid as 10%, 20%, 30% and 40% (i.e. 0.1gm/l, 0.2gm/l, 0.3gm/l and 0.4gm/l) were prepared [CITATION_1] . For the homogenous dispersion of nanoparticles, ferrofluid was ultra-sonicated for 30 minutes. Finally, to remove moisture, ferrofluid was kept in air circulated oven for 24 hours at 120\u2070C. Figure 1represents the schematic diagram of steps involved in the preparation of ferrofluid andFigure 2 shows the photograph of the ferrofluids prepared at various concentration. ",
